         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/12/88 ¶  ¶ With renewed delight, ¶  dear Mr Dyer, I express my words of deep gratitude for all you have done for Australia in my individuality, to see on the Science of this continent one of the gr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.12.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, ff. 267-8.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/12/88<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped</seg>: Royal Gardens Kew 28. Jan 89.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With renewed delight,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 7 November 1888.</p>
               </note> dear Mr Dyer, I express my words of deep gratitude for all you have done for Australia in my individuality, to see on the Science of this continent one of the grandest honors bestowed, within the scope of the great British forum of science for distribution.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Only your letter<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> now makes it fully clear, how select this bestowal is; and I must recognize, that many of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">most Worthy</hi>
               </seg> must pass away without this fascinating concatenation of great names touching them, simply because the gift is of such rarity and cannot reach all, who deserve it!<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mueller had been awarded a Royal Medal by the Royal Society of London. The Society awarded only two Royal Medals each year, covering all fields of science. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am quite touched with Sir Joseph's goodness, in thinking of me before already, a fact learned only now by me,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had been under consideration for the medal twenty years earlier, at the time Alfred Russel Wallace was awarded the 1868 Medal; see J. Hooker to C. Darwin, 17 May 1867, and C. Darwin to J. Hooker, 21 May 1867, in Burkhardt <seg style="font-style: italic; ">et al</seg>. (1985- ), vol. 15, pp. 262, 272. </p>
               </note> so that I am doubly beholden to your illustrious Socer.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Latin for 'father-in-law'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Quite charmed am I with the companionship of the Italian Astronomer and the British physiologist.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At the Royal Society's Anniversary Meeting on 30 November 1888, the Society's Copley Medal for that year was presented to the physiologist T. H. Huxley, the Rumford Medal to the Italian <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>astrophysicist Pietro Tacchini, and Royal Medals to M and the physicist Osborne Reynolds.</p>
               </note> The action of Mr Carruthers and particularly Dr Masters has been also most kind indeed.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to P. Sclater, December 1887, and notes thereto.</p>
               </note> As I am just preparing for the Presidential Adress in the therapeutic Section of the med. Congress<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Second Intercolonial Medical Congress of Australasia, Melbourne, 1889; see B89.13.16.</p>
               </note> for which several hundred names are enrolled and which will be held early in January I cannot write much, but add, that I hope ere long to show you by some continental honor my gratitude in a tangible manner.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully and gratefully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">When the official communication reaches me I shall fully endeavour to express my profound appreciation<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to G. Stokes, 1 January 1889.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Might not someone, going across to Denmark or other continental coast-places be shown the manner in which <name key="Kochia%20hirsuta">Kochia hirsuta</name> occurs along with <name key="Suaeda%20maritima">Suaeda maritima</name>. It would then be more hopeful to find it even when occuring in the almost glabrous form, as it may be quite [...]<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">illegible</seg> — word[s] obscured by binding.</p>
               </note> any how.<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The final paragraph is the only text on f. 268, and is placed here as it has the same date stamp as f. 267.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Kochia%20hirsuta">Kochia hirsuta</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Suaeda%20maritima">Suaeda maritima</name>
            </p>
         </div>
